public AuthorizationResponse(java.net.URL redirectURI)

redirectURI - The requested redirect URI. Must not be null.

toURL

public java.net.URL toURL()
                   throws SerializeException
Returns the URL representation (redirect URI + fragment / query string) of this authorisation response.

Example: 

 https://client.example.com/cb?code=Qcb0Orv1zh30vL1MPRsbm&state=af0ifjsldkj

Returns:
The URL representation of this authorisation response.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - If there is no authorisation code, UserInfo access token or ID token to serialise.
SerializeException - If this response couldn't be serialised to a URL.
